              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to experience a complete change in one’s way of life to what it should be, with the implication of return to a former state or relation</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be born again</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to experience new birth</Gloss>
                <Gloss>rebirth</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The metaphor of ‘new birth’ is so important in the NT that it should be retained if at all possible. In some languages ‘new birth’ can be expressed as ‘to cause to be born all over again’ or ‘to have a new life as though one were born a second time.’ See also {D:13.55}.</Comments>
